-- Zimbabwe Sold $30 Million in Diamonds After Kimberley Approval
-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m   a n d   G o d f r e y   M a r a w a n y i k a
-- 2012-02-16T18:08:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-16/zimbabwe-sold-30-million-in-diamonds-after-kimberley-approval.html
Zimbabwe sold diamonds worth $30
million in the past two weeks after receiving approval to sell
the gems from the  Kimberley Process , said Mines Minister  Obert
Mpofu .  The Diamond Mining Co (Pvt) Ltd., sold the gems in
Kimberley Process-approved sales, he told reporters today at the
Marange diamond fields in eastern Zimbabwe. The company is a
joint venture between Dubai-based Pure Diam and state-owned
Zimbabwe Mining Development Corp.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net ;
Godfrey Marawanyika in Harare at 
 gmarawanyika@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
